Dear friends & family,
My sincerest gratitude for all of your love and positivity on this summer's day! My cheeks hurt from smiling so much, and my soul feels uplifted with a joyful lightness of being.

Last year I revealed a goal to fully embrace my beauty & I continue to nurture a sort of inner peace with my 'uniqueness'. This year at 24, I am choosing to focus on Vulnerability. To be free from the shackles of fear and shyness, but instead, to step into unknown fires & emotional waters without hesitation. On a daily basis, I often feel & lead with my heart, while my mind orders to stay in the safe zone! Well, lately I am finally beginning to feel ready to allow more people to see the depths of my soul - to live honestly and without regrets! 
Love & Light,
Cheyenne Xo

En gutt stikker hodet frem ogs?går han inn. "Sa jeg at du kunne komme inn?!" hveser jeg. "Felly, det er Toby" sier Toby. Jeg kan kjenne igjen den mørke men trygge stemmen hvor som helst. "Det har ingenting ?si, jeg kunne like s?godt ha vært naken" mumler jeg irritert. "Jeg ville bare si unnskyld for at jeg gikk. Du vet, det er jo veldig store nyheter, det med kreft. Jo ogs? ehh-eh.. Jeg hadde, ehh tenkt til ?ehh, fri til deg" sier han og ser ned i bakken. Han tar hendene i lommene og sparker med den høyre foten mot bakken. Jeg måper. En stor, hard klump stiger opp i halsen min. Jeg begynner ?gråte. Toby ser opp og kommer bort til meg. Han setter seg p?sengekanten. Han omfavner meg hardt. Jeg legger armene rundt han og gråter p?skulderen min. Jeg elsker ?ha kroppen hans inntil min, ?kjenne tryggheten hans, ?kjenne at han alltid passer p?meg. "Jeg har lyst til ?gifte meg med deg" sier jeg og tørker bort de siste tårene. "Har du?" Han trekker seg litt unna. "Ja, s?klart! Du er den perfekte for meg. Og, jo s?elsker jeg deg Toby" smiler jeg. Han smiler stort. "Jeg elsker deg ogs? Felicia" sier han og kysser meg hardt og lenge.

When I saw the Eiffel Tower for the first time, I was overcome with emotion. As the symbol of France, it culminated all the feelings I had toward this trip into one single moment. For years before this I had seen the structure in my french books, on TV, in magazines, etc. Ever since I was a child and my mom used to tell me how she saw the Eiffel Tower and went all the way to the top, I had always dreamt of coming to Paris and seeing it for myself. I will be honest, I sat staring at the tower for a good 30 mins after I took this photo...I had finally realized a dream of mine. Anything you put your mind to is possible. yesterday, just in front of the eiffel tower despite the awful weather, a global protest was held against china. filipinos were joined by tibetans in their quest for freedom. i myself, have seen major demonstrations back in the university belt where i've spent my college days but never did i indulge myself in such activities. though i may believe on what they are fighting for, i know there are other ways i can be of help. but yday, my colleagues convinced me to even just a minute to be here. and then as they sang these phrases "Ang bayan ko'y tanging ikaw
Pilipinas Kong Mahal
Ang puso ko at buhay man
Sa iyo'y ibibigay
Tungkulin kong gagampanan
Na lagi kang paglingkuran
Ang laya mo'y babantayan
Pilipinas kong Hirang..." my tears started to pour down. we were thought of this song during our younger years but it is only as of this day that all of those lyrics made sense to me. tungkulin ko'y gagampanan, na lagi kang paglingkuran, ang laya mo'y babantayan... i remember my great grandfather who was a member of the Hukbalahap, he fought for our country, i hope standing here, i had my share too. ?????? #ilovephilippines #filipina #pinoyproud

I've learned so much about myself, about cuisine, about organic and food sustainability practices, and the French culture. It's very bittersweet having to leave today; I'm excited to go home and see everyone and experience American life again, but I'll also miss everything about my experience in Europe.

today's lesson comes from my adventure in Paris. It's so sappy to take your boyfriend to "the city of love", but I'm a complete, tragic, hopeless romantic. Perhaps I've watched Midnight In Paris too many times, but this moment at the Eiffel Tower in the rain can only be described as magic. Reflecting upon it now, it showed me that love, true love, transcends all. Wether it be state lines, country lines, family, friends, work, butting personalities, atypical lifestyles, pure craziness, love always has a funny way of making things work. Love doesn't know distance, or what else is going on in your life, it's an unstoppable force that pays no regard to time. And maybe that's the most terrifying thing about it; you're either ready or you're not. So my advice to you all today; ready or not, love is not something you can put aside for another time. You're a fool if something great comes to you and you don't take it. So go out today and tell someone that you love them, love always has it's funny way of making the unready, ready.

Feng Shui #101

La Tour Eiffel

The opposite of good #Qi is known as shar Qi or killing breath. The practice of #FengShui includes deflecting this negative #energy that can be caused by landscape orientations, harmful structures pointing or facing the home, office or public buildings, as well as incorrect arrangements of furniture and other objects inside a given space.

Poison arrows are thought to include; corners of neighbouring buildings facing directly at your building, a single tree or post facing your front door blocking good Qi from entering your home. A cross on a church facing your front door or in view from your windows.

The best known example of a building emitting Shar Qi in #HongKong of course is the #BankofChinaBuilding in Central. Whilst on a recent trip to #Paris I visited La Tour de Eiffel, curious to examine what effect the most visited #monument in the world may have on the city.

The tower is one of the finest examples of #Decorative arts in #Europe, comprising of four lattice girders standing apart at the base and coming together at the top, joined together by metal trusses at regular intervals. Observed from underneath and at distance, the #balance of the tower seems #harmonious and is of course perfectly #engineered.

Observed from a micro level the tower does not exert any Shar Qi. From a Macro Level the entrance to the structure is literally embraced by the The Trocadéro, Palais de Chaillot and the River Seine. No surprise that couples flock towards this site, even the surrounding #architecture exhibits a tangible sense of #romance. I noticed how the decorative forms within the lattice work reflects both #yin [female] and #yang [male] forms. In addition, the four standing legs are curved in form and retractive in their energy. The only obvious shar Qi may be emitted from the point of the needle capping the #cupola. As it directs upwards it is of no danger to the surrounding buildings and thus inhabitants. From a scale perspective, the Champ de Mars provides enough expanse from the École Militaire for any impact on this neighbouring major site. My analysis concludes that La Tour Eiffel really is the Ambassador of the Paris #skyline ??

Voltando para o Brasil, de férias na Europa, meu voo foi alterado e tive uma escala de mais tempo do que o previsto na cidade luz, no aeroporto Charles De Gaulle. Eu fiquei muito feliz, pois afinal, seria mais um país conquistado (de certa forma), porque nunca havia estado na França, j?meu marido não ficou muito animado, porque bateu aquela insegurança, ser?que d?tempo de sair e voltar para o aeroporto sem perder o voo de volta?? Depois de muita insistência minha (mulheres me entendem n? l?fomos nós para uma aventura, e que aventura! Nossa escala era de 6 horas. Parece bastante, não ?! Mas o aeroporto fica a +/- 30 km de Paris, longe dos principais pontos turísticos. Então, tivemos que escolher apenas um lugar para visitar, e nós não tivemos dúvidas.. qual o maior símbolo de Paris? A TORRE EIFFEL, ?claro!! O trânsito ?intenso em Paris, então taxi e bus não seriam boas escolhas, pois estávamos apenas com bagagem de mão. Ao contrário dos muitos comentários negativos que ouvimos sobre os franceses, tive uma impressão diferente. No primeiro trem, um senhor muito prestativo, desceu na estação que eu deveria descer s?para me explicar como eu fazia para pegar o próximo metr? Deve ser uma m?fama, pois minha impressão foi de parisienses amistosos e bem prestativos. Os trens são antigos, mas são muito eficientes. A torre fica pertinho da estação, nem 5 min. a p? a dificuldade est?em se conseguir boas fotos, pois são muitos turistas por aquele pedaço, mas vou contar... meus olhos encheram d’agua quando a vi de perto, s?estando l?pra saber.
